@echo off\n\nREM Enabling HTTP compression in IIS 6.0\n\ncd \inetpub\adminscripts\n\necho Enabling Static Compression...\ncscript adsutil.vbs set w3svc/filters/compression/parameters/HcDoStaticCompression True\n\necho Enabling Dynamic Compression...\ncscript adsutil.vbs set W3SVC/Filters/Compression/Parameters/HcDoDynamicCompression True\n\nREM Set the extensions for static compression\ncscript adsutil.vbs set w3svc/filters/compression/gzip/hcdynamiccompressionlevel 5\ncscript adsutil.vbs set w3svc/filters/compression/deflate/hcdynamiccompressionlevel 0\ncscript adsutil.vbs set w3svc/filters/compression/gzip/hcstaticcompressionlevel 9\ncscript adsutil.vbs set w3svc/filters/compression/deflate/hcstaticcompressionlevel 1\n\ncscript adsutil.vbs append w3svc/filters/compression/parameters/HcFileExtensions css\ncscript adsutil.vbs append w3svc/filters/compression/parameters/HcFileExtensions txt\ncscript adsutil.vbs append w3svc/filters/compression/parameters/HcFileExtensions html\ncscript adsutil.vbs append w3svc/filters/compression/parameters/HcFileExtensions js\n\necho Compression has been enabled.